<BaseLayout title="Symbols" description="Public symbols of Vaelinya.">
  <section class="page-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Artefacts</p>
    <h1>Symbols</h1>
    <p class="lede">Symbols carry memory, identity, and recognition across the world of Vaelinya.</p>
    <p>A symbol may be worn, carved, drawn, printed, remembered, or recognised in a story. It gives a reader something small and visible to hold onto while the world grows larger.</p>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">First symbol</p>
      <h2>NAVAN — Remember</h2>
      <p>NAVAN means “Remember.” It is the first public symbol-word because it carries one of Vaelinya’s clearest ideas: what matters should be carried forward with care.</p>
      <p>As a mark, NAVAN can belong with memory, return, witness, truth, and the work of keeping something from being lost.</p>
      <p><a class="button" href="/language/lexicon/">Read NAVAN in the lexicon</a></p>
    </article>

    <div class="link-list">
      <a href="/language/lexicon/">Words behind symbols</a>
      <a href="/artefacts/story-objects/">Story objects</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
